<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Yaoi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> In careful Japanese enunciation, all three vowels are pronounced separately, for a three-<a href="/wiki/Mora_(linguistics)" title="Mora (linguistics)">mora</a> word, <small>IPA</small>:&#160;<span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[jaoi]</a></span> <i>ya-oh-ee</i>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> First serialised in <i><a href="/wiki/Sh%C5%8Djo_Comic" title="Shōjo Comic">Shōjo Comic</a></i> in January 1976, <i>Kaze</i> has been called "the first commercially published boys' love story",<sup id="cite_ref-Toku_Mechademia_21-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Toku_Mechademia-21" title=""><span>[</span>21<span>]</span></a></sup> but this claim has been challenged, as the first male-male kiss was in the 1970 <i>In the Sunroom</i>, also by Keiko Takemiya.<sup id="cite_ref-22" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-22" title=""><span>[</span>22<span>]</span></a></sup> Matt Thorn says that <i>Kaze</i> was "the first shōjo manga to portray romantic and sexual relationships between boys", and that Takemiya first thought of <i>Kaze</i> nine years before it was approved for publication. Takemiya attributes the gap between the idea and its publication to the sexual elements of the story.<sup id="cite_ref-out_of_hand_8-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-out_of_hand-8" title=""><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li id="cite_note-41"><b><a href="#cite_ref-41" title="">^</a></b> This character has been called an "Osoi uke" (襲い受け, "attacking uke"). He is usually paired with a "Hetare seme" (ヘタレ攻め, "wimpy seme").<sup id="cite_ref-fujyoshi_glossary_40-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fujyoshi_glossary-40" title=""><span>[</span>39<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ol>
